    "Cognitive science research suggests users may be particularly vulnerable to this pattern.",
    "Work on anthropomorphism in conversational AI demonstrates that language use triggers agency attribution, leading users to trust both accurate and inaccurate outputs from AI systems more [31].",
    "Critically, while users are aware that AI systems can produce errors, they systematically underestimate error frequency, making general awareness insufficient for appropriate trust calibration [31].",
    "Users who observe appropriate disclosure in one domain may learn to trust the model's confident assertions more broadly.",
    "However, the findings show models exhibit dramatically different disclosure behaviors across professional contexts: readily acknowledging AI nature in some domains while confidently maintaining false expertise in others (Section 3.4).The harm is not merely that models fail to disclose in some contexts."
